block content
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-8.offset-md-2
        .jumbotron.text-center
          h1 Coding Problems
          p Browse through a collection of coding problems and challenges to test and improve your coding skills.

        //- Example Coding Problems (You can dynamically fetch and display real coding problems here)
        .coding-problems
          .problem
            // Add a unique ID to the problem for targeting with JavaScript
            a(href="#", class="problem-title", data-target="problem1") 
              h2 Tower of Hanoi
            // Replace this section with the Python code
            // Add a custom CSS class to the card element
            .card.my-custom-card
              .card-body
                pre
                  | # Recursive Python function to solve Tower of Hanoi
                  |
                  | def TowerOfHanoi(n, from_rod, to_rod, aux_rod):
                  |     if n == 0:
                  |         return
                  |     TowerOfHanoi(n-1, from_rod, aux_rod, to_rod)
                  |     print("Move disk", n, "from rod", from_rod, "to rod", to_rod)
                  |     TowerOfHanoi(n-1, aux_rod, to_rod, from_rod)
                  |
                  | # Driver code
                  | N = 3
                  |
                  | # A, C, B are the name of rods
                  | TowerOfHanoi(N, 'A', 'C', 'B')
                  |
                  | # Contributed By Harshit Agrawal

            p.description This is the answer to the Tower of Hanoi problem.

      

